definitions.definition: Rod - shaped : straight , long , and thin , ( particularly botany ) the habitus of plants with straight , erect branches .
Finely striped , often with dark fibers .

main_definition: Rod - shaped : straight , long , and thin , ( particularly botany ) the habitus of plants with straight , erect branches .
